<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-09-0721 </DOCNO><TEXT>New semiconductor technologies have led to a continuous increase of automotiveelectronics, that the service shops must cope with, today and above allin the next years. As a tool for exact fault localization in the car,the onboard diagnosis was introduced in BMW automobiles. Via a two linewire all electronic control units containing a microcomputer are connectedto each other and can be questioned systematically for faults by thetest equipment. The concept of the data exchange is so, that the informationcan be transmitted not only with fixed but also with variable baudrates.Therefore, the onboard diagnosis gives an important distribution fora complete integrated service concept.</TEXT></DOC>